In case you missed it, here are the top Sport stories of the week: 1. BAXTER SEES THE LIGHT Kaizer Chiefs have started the year slowly, first getting dumped out of the Nedbank Cup before producing another timid display in the DStv Premiership in their 0-0 draw against Cape Town on Tuesday night. 2. PYRAMIDS SET TO SNATCH USUTHU STAR! Amazulu could lose their budding star Siphesihle Maduna to top Egqptian club Pyramids who are monitoring the midfielder's progress. 3. CHIEFS ANNOUNCE NEW SPONSOR Kaizer Chiefs have announced that their existing partnership agreement with Toyota will now include the manufacturer's logo on the Amakhosi jersey. 4. MULENGA FRUSTRATES BENNI! Amazulu coach Benni McCarthy has revealed star striker Augustine Mulenga's dip in form could be attributed to the fact that the striker enjoyed a great partnership with Sibusiso Mabiliso last season. 5. CHIEFS SET TO WELCOME BACK STAR DEFENDER Kaizer Chiefs, who are going through another bad patch this season, have had some good news with the possible return to training of star left-back Sifiso Hlanti.